Bugs caught LIVE during F.10 (none would have been caught by unit
tests — they're all about Composio API shape, not adapter logic):

  Bug 1: api/src/routes/automations.ts passed `composioUserId: ws`
    (workspace_id) to reconcileTriggers, which then INSERTed the
    workspace_id into composio_poll_state.composio_user_id. But
    Composio's connected_account is owned by an `entity_id` that
    equals the account_id (per loadConnectedAccountByToolkit's
    lookup convention). On the cron-kicker's first sweep, the
    adapter's GOOGLESHEETS_BATCH_GET call failed with HTTP 400
    `ConnectedAccountEntityIdMismatch`. FIX: pass account_id to
    composioUserId at all three reconcile call-sites.
  Bug 2: gmail adapter used Composio tool slugs that don't exist —
    `GMAIL_FETCH_USER_PROFILE` and `GMAIL_LIST_HISTORY` both 404
    against Composio's v3.1 API. Their tool catalog doesn't expose
    Gmail's history-delta API; only `GMAIL_FETCH_EMAILS` with a
    Gmail-query string (after:<unix_secs>). REWROTE the adapter:
    state is `{ last_seen_unix, last_seen_message_ids }`; poll
    builds a `after:<lastSeen-300>` query (300s slack window for
    Gmail indexing lag), dedupes by message-id ring (cap 200).
    Rewrote the test file to match — 12 specs covering baseline,
    no-change, single-new, dedupe-by-id-ring, from-filter (now
    `(from:a OR from:b)` query syntax), label-filter, include_body,
    slack-window correctness, missing-state recovery, HTTP error,
    envelope-shape resilience.
  Bug 3: Composio's response envelope is INCONSISTENT per tool —
    some return `data.response_data.<x>`, others return `data.<x>`
    directly. F.10's first sweep had the googlesheets adapter
    silently parse 0 rows (couldn't find valueRanges under
    response_data). Pre-emptively fixed in ALL five adapters
    (googlesheets, gmail, googlecalendar, googledrive, notion,
    airtable) — each callTool now checks both shapes.

