Operator-observed events during the run (for the record):
  1. "Got an SMS approval text 'F.10: sheets trigger fired' when
     I approved" — TRIGGERED accidentally by the stale-state
     boundary on v3→v4 transition. The googlesheets adapter
     parsed the response envelope wrong (Bug 3), stored
     last_row_count=0, then the redeploy with the fixed envelope
     parser counted current=1 → emitted the header row as a
     phantom event. After v4 clean-baseline created on fixed
     code, no further phantom fires. Proved the pipeline works
     even on the false-positive path.
  2. "Got SMS but it fired twice for one email" — both gmail
     SMSes were legitimate: one for the operator's test email,
     one for a Twitch promo that arrived in the 5-min slack
     window. The automation's gmail filter was `{}` (no filter)
     so any new message in the inbox triggers. Documented as
     expected behavior of an unfiltered gmail trigger.

